	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Are there any trackers for Namco's WSG audio unit?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Konami SCC is also similar, with 32-step waveforms, but I believe it has 5 channels and the samples are 8-bit.  It's used on some MSX2 cartridges.  I'm sure there must be a tracker for it, but I wouldn't know what one to recommend.  I would recommend checking out the music in Metal Gear 2 though, it uses that chip and is one of my favorite game soundtracks.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


